Gunmen on Saturday, invaded the family house of the Edo State Deputy Governor, Dr. Philip Shaibu. Shaibu who hails from Jattu in Estako West local government area, built his country home opposite his family house. It was gathered that residents in the house were sleeping when the gunmen struck. Witnesses say neighbours were able to chase the gunmen away and one of them was eventually arrested. The name of the arrested suspect was given as Victor John. One of the suspects identified as Emeka however escaped. A family source said it was policemen at Shaibuâ€™s residence that arrested Victor after they scaled the fence. The source said Victor led them to his house where other suspects were arrested. When contacted, Shaibu confirmed the incidence and said the suspects were already making statements at the police station. It was learnt that the suspects were being transferred to the State Criminal Investigation Department (SCID) for further interrogation. 